---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Waitlist from '../components/sections/Waitlist.astro';
import WaitlistForm from '../components/forms/WaitlistForm.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Couples Food System" description="Our story — why we built Couples Food System and our mission to remove the mental load of meal planning.">
  <section class="py-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-6">Our Story</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Brand Story Image -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg border border-border mb-12">
      <img src="/images/hero/about-story.webp" alt="A couple's hands preparing fresh vegetables together on a wooden table in a sun-drenched kitchen with sage green and terracotta accents" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 md:p-16 rounded-2xl border border-border shadow-sm space-y-6 text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        It started in our own kitchen. I wanted to lean out, and my partner wanted to build muscle. Suddenly, Sunday meal prep became a nightmare of two different recipes, two grocery lists, and twice the cleanup.
      </p>
      <p>
        We tried standard meal planning apps, but they felt clinical, isolating, and completely ignored the fact that cooking together is supposed to be a bonding experience, not a math equation.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's why we built <strong class="text-text-primary font-semibold">Couples Food System</strong>. We believe that sharing a meal is a cornerstone of a healthy relationship. Our mission is to remove the mental load of meal planning and the friction of dietary differences, so you can get back to what matters: enjoying dinner together.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Waitlist>
    <WaitlistForm />
  </Waitlist>
</BaseLayout>
